<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,1537,1563]" pageId="45" pageNumber="70">Notes:—</emphasis>
We saw this species growing in gardens on the islands of 
<collectingCountry box="[883,981,1537,1563]" name="Grenada" pageId="45" pageNumber="70">Grenada</collectingCountry>
, Carriacou, and Petite 
<collectingCountry box="[1234,1361,1537,1563]" name="Martinique" pageId="45" pageNumber="70">Martinique</collectingCountry>
, but not elsewhere. We are following 
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor, N. P. &amp; Zappi, D. C." box="[458,711,1573,1599]" pageId="45" pageNumber="70" pagination="17 - 25" refId="ref18363" refString="Taylor, N. P. &amp; Zappi, D. C. (2019) Notes on plants called Cereus hexagonus (Cactaceae). Bradleya 37: 17 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.25223 / brad. n 37.2019. a 23" type="journal article" year="2019">Taylor &amp; Zappi (2019)</bibRefCitation>
in using the above name for this species. The plants grow tree-like to large dimensions, branches upright with blue-grey coloured stems. Rib 4–5, spineless or with very short spines.
</paragraph>
